 * The enumeration class representing the 12 months of the year.
 */
public expect enum class Month {
    /** January, month #01, with 31 days. */
    JANUARY,

    /** February, month #02, with 28 days, or 29 in leap years. */
    FEBRUARY,

    /** March, month #03, with 31 days. */
    MARCH,

    /** April, month #04, with 30 days. */
    APRIL,

    /** May, month #05, with 31 days. */
    MAY,

    /** June, month #06, with 30 days. */
    JUNE,

    /** July, month #07, with 31 days. */
    JULY,

    /** August, month #08, with 31 days. */
    AUGUST,

    /** September, month #09, with 30 days. */
    SEPTEMBER,

    /** October, month #10, with 31 days. */
    OCTOBER,

    /** November, month #11, with 30 days. */
    NOVEMBER,

    /** December, month #12, with 31 days. */
    DECEMBER;

//    val value: Int // member missing in java.time.Month has to be an extension
}", "new_string": "/**
 * The enumeration class representing the 12 months of the year.
 *
 * The months are numbered from 1 ([JANUARY]) to 12 ([DECEMBER]) according to ISO 8601 standard.
 * See the [number] property.
 *
 * ### Acquiring a [Month]
 *
 * A [Month] instance can be acquired using:
 * - The [LocalDate.month] property to get the month for a given date.
 * - The [LocalDateTime.month] property to get the month for a given date/time value.
 * - The [Month] factory function to construct by month number, e.g. `Month(8)` for August.
 * - The enum constant directly, e.g. `Month.AUGUST`.
 *
 * ### Using a [Month]
 *
 * When constructing a [LocalDate] or [LocalDateTime], use the [Month] enum directly:
 * ```
 * val date = LocalDate(2021, Month.AUGUST, 31)
 * ```
 * Alternatively, use the numeric month number directly:
 * ```
 * val date = LocalDate(2021, 8, 31)
 * ```
 *
 * ### Serialization
 *
 * This class is not serializable out of the box.
 * [kotlinx.serialization](https://github.com/Kotlin/kotlinx.serialization) does not support
 * [enumerations with `expect/actual` implementations](https://github.com/Kotlin/kotlinx.serialization/issues/2649).
 *
 * @sample kotlinx.datetime.test.samples.MonthSamples.usage
 */
public expect enum class Month {
    /** January, month 1 with 31 days. */
    JANUARY,

    /** February, month 2 with 28 days in a common year and 29 in a leap year. */
    FEBRUARY,

    /** March, month 3 with 31 days. */
    MARCH,

    /** April, month 4 with 30 days. */
    APRIL,

    /** May, month 5 with 31 days. */
    MAY,

    /** June, month 6 with 30 days. */
    JUNE,

    /** July, month 7 with 31 days. */
    JULY,

    /** August, month 8 with 31 days. */
    AUGUST,

    /** September, month 9 with 30 days. */
    SEPTEMBER,

    /** October, month 10 with 31 days. */
    OCTOBER,

    /** November, month 11 with 30 days. */
    NOVEMBER,

    /** December, month 12 with 31 days. */
    DECEMBER;
}"}

